 THE STUDENT PILOT REPORTED HE WAS BACK-TAXIING AFTER LANDING. HE 
ESTIMATED HIS TAXI SPEED AT 15 MPH. HE SAID HE WAS ATTEMPTING TO BRAKE 
AND TURN OFF THE RUNWAY ONTO THE TAXIWAY WHEN HE LOST DIRECTIONAL 
CONTROL AND THE AIRPLANE NOSED OVER. HE STATED THE ACCIDENT COULD 
HAVE BEEN PREVENTED IF HE HAD TAXIED AT A SLOWER SPEED. 
 AN EXCESSIVE TAXI SPEED. 
